## 3. Game Economy Rules

When touching economy logic, preserve these invariants:

- PC (Poxy Coin) is the primary currency — 1 PC = 1 unit, integer only
- PX (Poxy Points) are XP-like rewards — separate from PC
- Dust is burn reward currency — cannot be converted back to PC
- Anti-dump tax: 5% on OTC transfers — never remove this
- Founder discount is permanent and applies from London launch date
- Generation supply is fixed: Gen 0 = 1,000 · Gen 1 = 5,000
- Rarity weights: Common > Uncommon > Rare > Epic > Legendary > Mythic > Secret
- Craft ratio: 5x Common → 1x Uncommon (never change without explicit instruction)

---

## 4. Security Rules

- Never expose Supabase service_role key in client code
- All ownership checks happen server-side (RPC/Edge Functions) — never trust client
- Nonce + timestamp on every signed request — reject replays
- Session validation before every protected route render
- OTC air-gap: 24h freeze after new login — do not bypass in code
- Recovery keys shown once — never store in plaintext

---

## 5. Workflow Rules

### When asked to add a feature:
1. Read the existing relevant code section first
2. Identify what already exists to avoid duplication
3. Write the minimum code needed — no over-engineering
4. Preserve all existing CSS variables and class names
5. Test the mental model on mobile before suggesting

### When asked to fix a bug:
1. Identify root cause before touching code
2. Fix only what's broken — don't refactor surrounding code
3. State what you changed and why

### When asked to improve design:
1. Follow Sky v2 system (`DESIGN.md`, mockups in `design/v2/`)
2. Use `assets/poxy-sky/tokens.css` — no legacy pink/mint unless unmigrated screen
3. Animations CSS-only; respect `prefers-reduced-motion` and performance mode
4. Mobile-first; one stage at a time with test gate before next

### Commit message format:
```
feat(scope): short description
fix(scope): short description
style(ui): short description
refactor(crypto): short description
```

---

## 6. What POXY Is NOT

- NOT a standard SaaS dashboard — avoid that aesthetic entirely
- NOT a blockchain app (yet) — it's crypto-verified but centralized on Supabase
- NOT a React app — pure vanilla JS, no JSX, no virtual DOM
- NOT desktop-first — always mobile-first
- NOT a simple lootbox site — it's a full ecosystem with DAO, Club, Passport, OTC

